8. About FSL-1.1-MIT

   The Functional Source License is a non-OSI-approved source-available
   license maintained by Sentry. The canonical text and rationale live
   at https://fsl.software/. Dictivo chose this license for its
   straightforward two-year MIT conversion, which gives both immediate
   transparency for users auditing the privacy claims and a path to
   permanent open-sourcing without indefinite commercial restriction.
